    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can do this through Javascript.\nPlease take a look at this API: <a href=\"http://www.w3.org/TR/page-visibility/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">http://www.w3.org/TR/page-visibility/</a>\nSomeone asked a similar question:</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1060008/is-there-a-way-to-detect-if-a-browser-window-is-not-currently-active\">Is there a way to detect if a browser window is not currently active?</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "user_type" : "does_not_exist",
      "display_name" : "user3235186"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1437549246,
    "creation_date" : 1437549246,
    "answer_id" : 31556279,
    "question_id" : 31555910,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>To know if a new window/tab is opened,</p>\n\n<p>use onblur for the top most frame. [window.top]</p>\n\n<pre><code>window.top.onblur = function() { alert() }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>for resize, window.onresize should do the job.</p>\n"
  } ],
